node.text:
❤️
——
👇🏼 INGREDIENTS:
💥 ASSEMBLY
- 1 1/2 tablespoon melted butter
- 1 slightly beaten egg
- 1/2 cup peanut butter
- 1 1/2 cups almond milk
- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup
- 1 1/2 cups old fashioned rolled oats
- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder
- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
- 1/8 teaspoon salt
- 1/4 cup of strawberry or raspberry jam/jelly
——
👇🏼 INSTRUCTIONS:
- Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease a large skillet or 8x8 inch baking pan with coconut oil or generously spray with nonstick cooking spray.
- In a large bowl, add in melted and cooled coconut oil, peanut butter, honey, egg and almond milk. Whisk together until well combined and no large lumps of peanut butter remain.
- Fold in oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Pour into prepared skillet/pan and make sure oatmeal is evenly spread out.
- Drop jam by teaspoonful onto oatmeal bake, then very gently swirl.
- Bake for 30-35 minutes until barely golden brown.
- DIG IN WITH A SPOON❗
🎥: @dessertbae
📍: Orlando, Florida
🎵: "King" Jef
👇🏽TAG SOMEONE WHO LOVES PB&J👇🏽

node.text:
Frozen Yogurt Bark with Berries‼️ 🍓❄ The perfect refreshing snack. It’s so easy to whip up. You’ll want a batch in your freezer at all times 😍 #dessertbae ❤
⁣
💥INGREDIENTS💥
- 32 oz tub Vanilla yogurt 
- 1 cup fresh strawberries, sliced
- 1 cup fresh blueberries
- 1/2 cup granola
⁣
✨INSTRUCTIONS:
- Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.
- Spread yogurt mixture evenly, about a 1/4 of an inch thick, onto the prepared baking sheet in rectangular shape. Scatter the strawberries and blueberries on top. Sprinkle with granola.
- Place in the freezer for about 3 hours or until the yogurt is firm. Cut or break into 16-20 pieces and serve.
- Store leftover yogurt bark in a sealed freezer bag for up to 3 months. I like taking it out and letting it sit for about 3-5 minutes before eating.
- ENJOY! 😋
⁣
🎥: @dessertbae
📍: Orlando, Florida
👇🏽TAG SOMEONE WHO LOVES YOGURT

node.text:
LUCKY CHARMS SUGAR COOKIE DOUGH SKILLET‼️ 🍬🍪😋 With marshmallow bits & icing drizzled on top 🤤🙌🏽 #dessertbae ❤
⁣
💥INGREDIENTS💥 
- 1 pack of @pillsbury @luckycharms sugar cookie dough
- Icing for topping

✨INSTRUCTIONS✨
-  Preheat the oven to 325°F. Spray a skillet pan with pam
- Put cookie dough on the pan and bake for 20min
- Remove from the oven
- Drizzle icing all over it
- Get a spoon and dig in! ENJOY 😉

⁣
🎥: @dessertbae
👇🏽TAG SOMEONE WHO LOVES LUCKY CHARMS👇🏽

Limited-Edition Galactic Lucky Charms Marshmallow Treats‼️ 🍀🥣😋 Would you SMASH or PASS⁉️ 😏#dessertbae ❤
⁣
💥INGREDIENTS💥
- 3 tablespoon butter 
- 1 (10-oz.) bag marshmallows
- 1 box of Limited-Edition Galactic Lucky Charms cereal

✨INSTRUCTIONS✨
- Line a 9”-x-13” pan with parchment paper and grease with cooking spray. In a large pot over medium-low heat, melt butter. Stir in marshmallows until mixture is melted. Remove from heat.
- Immediately add @luckycharms and stir with a rubber spatula until combined. Working quickly, press the mixture into a pan and press evenly.
- Slice into squares and serve.
- ENJOY! 🤤

⁣
🎥: @dessertbae
👇🏽TAG SOMEONE WHO LOVES LUCKY CHARMS👇🏽
